One person has died and scores injured in a road crash after a bus and lorry collided head-on near Muhoroni junction on Kisumu-Kericho highway. Kericho County Police Commander James Mugera said the 67-seater bus which was ferrying passengers to Kisumu from Kericho was being driven carelessly. "It was around 3pm when the incident happened. The driver of the bus belonging to Rechcom Sacco was overtaking carelessly when it hit an oncoming lorry around the Rai Cement factory," said Mr Mugera. Those injured were rushed to various hospitals including Muhoroni, Ahero and Awasi while the body was taken to Kericho District Hospital mortuary.  